<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=17350&amp;p=218414#p218414"><![CDATA[
I've been arranging music in FamiTracker since 2009, but there's one little problem. I've been using the DPCM samples of SMB3 which are under copyright of Nintendo and which I'm not allowed to use because of the copyright as Fair Use won't save me. Has anyone had this problem? What have you used as a replacement? Since I've got used to the sound of my compositions with the samples, it will be hard to get used to some new samples so I'd need to have them sound with as little difference as possible while being enough different to not be infringing of Nintendo's copyright.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=6924">8bitMicroGuy</a> — Sat May 12, 2018 1:02 pm</p><hr />
